01:04:27.446 --> 01:04:28.864
<i>Good, I'm bringing a guest.</i>

01:04:28.948 --> 01:04:31.408
<i>Well, won't Kitty Haynes be surprised.</i>

01:04:35.621 --> 01:04:38.373
<i>- Table for seven, please, Arturo.
- Yes, sir.</i>

01:04:39.083 --> 01:04:40.542
<i>- Seven?
- Seven.</i>

01:04:40.626 --> 01:04:43.128
<i>That's impossible. It's always six.</i>

01:04:43.170 --> 01:04:45.046
<i>We have an extra.</i>

01:04:45.131 --> 01:04:46.631
<i>Seven, Arturo.</i>

01:04:48.301 --> 01:04:49.676
<i>This person?</i>

01:04:52.597 --> 01:04:56.224
<i>So let's not speak of love sublime</i>

01:04:56.309 --> 01:05:00.729
<i>Because time brings on a breakup</i>

01:05:02.940 --> 01:05:08.236
<i>There'll be no tears
and no emotional scenes</i>

01:05:08.321 --> 01:05:11.323
<i>To spoil my makeup</i>

01:05:13.284 --> 01:05:15.994
<i>And when the end comes</i>

01:05:16.037 --> 01:05:18.163
<i>I'll take up the slack</i>

01:05:18.205 --> 01:05:19.581
<i>Would you like some more champagne?</i>

01:05:19.665 --> 01:05:21.416
<i>Oh, thank you.</i>

01:05:21.500 --> 01:05:23.585
<i>Listen, Tom,
I don't know what they're charging you,</i>

01:05:23.669 --> 01:05:26.546
<i>but those champagne
bottles are filled with ginger ale.</i>

01:05:26.631 --> 01:05:28.381
<i>- That's the movies, kid!
- Shh.</i>

01:05:28.466 --> 01:05:31.301
<i>Oh, I don't care. I love every minute of it.</i>

01:05:34.680 --> 01:05:39.684
<i>Every Sunday, Monday</i>

01:05:39.727 --> 01:05:46.524
<i>One day at a time</i>

01:05:49.195 --> 01:05:53.657
<i>Let's take it one day at a time</i>

01:05:56.535 --> 01:05:57.994
<i>Let's take it</i>

01:05:58.037 --> 01:06:05.043
<i>One day at a time</i>

01:06:08.965 --> 01:06:10.840
MAN: <i>Bravo! Bravo!</i>

01:06:16.347 --> 01:06:18.682
<i>Thank you, thank you.</i>

01:06:19.100 --> 01:06:22.394
<i>- Who are you?
- Oh, no, I'm... I just... I came with Tom.</i>

01:06:22.478 --> 01:06:24.396
<i>You sing so beautifully.</i>

01:06:25.898 --> 01:06:27.315
<i>What the hell is this?</i>

01:06:27.400 --> 01:06:28.984
<i>We're supposed to meet and marry.</i>

01:06:29.068 --> 01:06:31.152
<i>- Who's the skirt?
- My fiance.</i>

01:06:31.237 --> 01:06:32.404
<i>- What?
- Oh, no, wait...</i>

01:06:32.488 --> 01:06:34.197
- HENRY: <i>He met her in New Jersey.
- What is this?</i>

01:06:34.240 --> 01:06:35.907
<i>Kitty, she's real.</i>

01:06:41.038 --> 01:06:42.288
- (SCREAMS)
- COUNTESS: <i>Kitty!</i>

01:06:42.373 --> 01:06:44.708
<i>Quick! Pour... Pour ginger ale on her!</i>

01:06:44.750 --> 01:06:46.001
<i>What's all the fuss about?</i>

01:06:46.085 --> 01:06:47.794
<i>Uh, nothing, nothing, Arturo.</i>

01:06:47.878 --> 01:06:50.338
<i>- We were just leaving. Come on. Let's go.
- Leaving? Leaving where?</i>

01:06:50.423 --> 01:06:51.923
<i>Hey, I'm all mixed up!</i>

01:06:52.008 --> 01:06:53.591
<i>I'm gonna show Cecilia the town.</i>

01:06:53.676 --> 01:06:55.885
<i>Are we just chucking out the plot, sir?</i>

01:06:55.928 --> 01:06:58.430
<i>Exactly. It's every man for himself!</i>

01:06:59.306 --> 01:07:01.141
<i>Then I don't have to seat people anymore.</i>

01:07:01.225 --> 01:07:03.351
<i>I can do what it is I've always wanted to do.</i>

01:07:03.436 --> 01:07:04.519
<i>What's that?</i>

01:07:04.603 --> 01:07:05.603
<i>Hit it, boys!</i>

01:07:05.646 --> 01:07:07.188
(MUSIC PLAYING)

01:07:14.113 --> 01:07:15.822
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

01:08:20.011 --> 01:08:22.555
<i>I had such a wonderful time.</i>

01:08:22.640 --> 01:08:23.973
<i>Me, too.</i>

01:08:24.642 --> 01:08:26.017
<i>Where are all the others?</i>

01:08:26.102 --> 01:08:29.979
<i>Oh, I don't know.
Well, probably just still dancing away.</i>

01:08:31.232 --> 01:08:34.234
<i>Why? Does it matter?
I wanted to get you alone.</i>

01:08:34.318 --> 01:08:36.194
<i>It's so beautiful here.</i>

01:08:38.447 --> 01:08:41.032
<i>Oh! The white telephone.</i>

01:08:41.075 --> 01:08:42.200
<i>Oh...</i>

01:08:43.368 --> 01:08:46.037
<i>I've dreamed of having a white telephone.</i>

01:08:46.122 --> 01:08:48.163
<i>Your dreams are my dreams.</i>

01:08:48.207 --> 01:08:49.624
<i>My whole life, I've wondered</i>

01:08:49.707 --> 01:08:52.335
<i>what it would be like
to be this side of the screen.</i>

01:08:52.377 --> 01:08:54.962
<i>You see that city out there waking up?</i>

01:08:55.046 --> 01:08:57.465
<i>That's yours for the asking.</i>

01:08:57.550 --> 01:08:59.551
<i>My heart's beating so fast!</i>

01:09:06.183 --> 01:09:07.767
GIL: Cecilia!

01:09:08.935 --> 01:09:11.563
<i>Gil! What are you doing here?</i>

01:09:11.647 --> 01:09:13.398
Well, I... I came in here to think.

01:09:13.482 --> 01:09:14.899
What are you doing here?

01:09:14.984 --> 01:09:17.527
<i>I took her on a date, all right?</i>

01:09:17.569 --> 01:09:19.194
<i>Now, can't you just leave us alone?</i>

01:09:19.238 --> 01:09:21.363
No, I can't leave her alone.

01:09:22.158 --> 01:09:23.533
I'm jealous.

01:09:23.576 --> 01:09:25.118
<i>You're jealous?</i>

01:09:25.202 --> 01:09:26.202
Well, what do you want me to say?

01:09:26.245 --> 01:09:28.912
I can't get Cecilia out of my mind.

01:09:28.956 --> 01:09:30.747
<i>Gil, do you mean that?</i>

01:09:30.791 --> 01:09:34.460
<i>Oh, for God's sake,
would you go back to Hollywood? Please.</i>

01:09:34.545 --> 01:09:37.171
Look, I'm embarrassed to admit it, Cecilia.

01:09:37.673 --> 01:09:39.883
You know, you said I had a magical glow?

01:09:39.925 --> 01:09:43.094
But that's you, you're the one that has one.

01:09:43.136 --> 01:09:46.890
And even though we've just met,
I know that this is the real thing.

01:09:46.932 --> 01:09:49.934
You can't be in love with Cecilia.
She's in love with me.

01:09:50.019 --> 01:09:52.270
I'll tell you what, why don't you
turn around and re-enter the film?

01:09:52.354 --> 01:09:53.604
I'm never going back!

01:09:53.647 --> 01:09:55.607
<i>I can't believe it, they're at it again.</i>

01:09:55.691 --> 01:09:57.942
<i>Tom, will you get back up here?</i>

01:09:57.985 --> 01:10:00.111
See, there you go, Tom.
You're ruining everything.

01:10:00.154 --> 01:10:01.696
You are!
You're the one who's ruining everything.

01:10:01.780 --> 01:10:03.364
You know, if it wasn't for me,
there wouldn't be any you!

01:10:03.449 --> 01:10:04.991
Don't be so sure! I could've been played

01:10:05.075 --> 01:10:06.910
by Fredric March or Leslie Howard!

01:10:06.952 --> 01:10:10.705
<i>You're wrong. The part's
too insignificant to attract a major star.</i>

01:10:10.789 --> 01:10:13.249
- Insignificant!
- Like hell it is! What are you talking about?

01:10:13.292 --> 01:10:14.751
Minor character?
I am not a minor character!

01:10:14.793 --> 01:10:15.919
What do you mean, a minor character?

01:10:15.961 --> 01:10:17.212
Jeez!

01:10:17.296 --> 01:10:19.631
You know, I haven't
been able to think of anything since we met.

01:10:19.715 --> 01:10:23.468
I just, I have to have some time with you
to show you what real life can be like

01:10:23.510 --> 01:10:26.262
if two people really care for each other.

01:10:27.431 --> 01:10:29.057
Last week, I was unloved.

01:10:29.141 --> 01:10:33.478
Now, two people love me,
and it's the same two people.

01:10:33.562 --> 01:10:35.647
<i>Go with the real guy, honey. We're limited.</i>

01:10:35.689 --> 01:10:37.857
<i>Go with Tom. He's got no flaws.</i>

01:10:37.942 --> 01:10:40.318
<i>Go with somebody, child,
'cause I's getting bored.</i>

01:10:40.778 --> 01:10:43.112
She's gonna marry me.
You're just... You're wasting your time.

01:10:43.155 --> 01:10:45.198
Will you get back on the screen?

01:10:45.282 --> 01:10:47.533
I'm trying to tell Cecilia I'm in love with her.

01:10:47.618 --> 01:10:50.995
I love you.
I'm honest, dependable, courageous,

01:10:51.080 --> 01:10:53.081
romantic and a great kisser.

01:10:53.165 --> 01:10:54.249
And I'm real!

01:10:54.333 --> 01:10:56.000
LARRY: <i>Let's go, Cecilia!</i>

01:10:56.085 --> 01:10:58.628
<i>Choose one of them
so we can settle this thing.</i>

01:10:58.671 --> 01:11:01.673
<i>The most human of all attributes
is your ability to choose.</i>

01:11:01.715 --> 01:11:03.132
<i>Well, wait a minute. Wait a minute.</i>

01:11:03.175 --> 01:11:05.677
<i>If she chooses Tom,
how are we gonna end the story?</i>

01:11:05.719 --> 01:11:07.136
<i>We'll be stuck here forever.</i>

01:11:07.179 --> 01:11:09.681
Father Donnelly can
marry us right here in the movie house.

01:11:09.765 --> 01:11:11.015
No, that won't stand up in court.

01:11:11.058 --> 01:11:12.350
The priest has to be human.

01:11:12.434 --> 01:11:14.936
<i>The Bible never says
a priest can't be on film!</i>

01:11:15.020 --> 01:11:17.397
No, uh, I'm already married!

01:11:17.481 --> 01:11:19.274
Come away with me to Hollywood.

01:11:19.358 --> 01:11:21.609
- Just like that?
- Just like that.

01:11:21.694 --> 01:11:23.861
Do something impulsive
for once in your life.

01:11:23.904 --> 01:11:28.283
I mean, just throw your stuff in a valise
and come away with me. Really.

01:11:28.367 --> 01:11:29.867
(CHUCKLING) And don't forget that ukulele.

01:11:30.035 --> 01:11:31.536
What ukulele?

01:11:31.578 --> 01:11:33.121
Look, I love you.

01:11:33.205 --> 01:11:37.208
I know that only happens in movies,
but I do.

01:11:42.214 --> 01:11:43.298
Tom?

01:11:45.009 --> 01:11:47.093
<i>Cecilia, you're throwing away perfection.</i>

01:11:47.177 --> 01:11:49.679
<i>Don't tell her that! We need Tom back!</i>

01:11:49.722 --> 01:11:51.306
<i>It's so romantic.</i>

01:11:51.390 --> 01:11:52.640
<i>Oh, women!</i>

01:11:52.725 --> 01:11:53.891
(SIGHS)

01:11:55.602 --> 01:11:58.730
Well, I'm crushed, I'm devastated. It's...

01:12:00.649 --> 01:12:02.650
Tom, try to understand.

01:12:04.069 --> 01:12:05.486
You'll be fine.

01:12:05.571 --> 01:12:09.157
In your world, things have a way
of always working out right.

01:12:09.241 --> 01:12:10.867
See, I'm a real person.

01:12:10.909 --> 01:12:16.164
No matter how tempted I am,
I have to choose the real world.

01:12:17.416 --> 01:12:19.751
I loved every minute with you.

01:12:21.003 --> 01:12:23.921
And I'll never forget our night on the town.

01:12:27.718 --> 01:12:28.926
Goodbye.

01:12:40.898 --> 01:12:44.442
HENRY: <i>Well, you're better off with us,
old sport, you really are.</i>

01:12:44.526 --> 01:12:46.778
JASON: <i>Can we get on
with</i> The Purple Rose of Cairo, <i>please?</i>

01:12:46.820 --> 01:12:49.030
COUNTESS: <i>If anyone wants me,
I'll be in reel six.</i>

01:12:49.114 --> 01:12:51.699
<i>- Kitty's waiting for you.</i>
- DELILAH: <i>Lord have mercy!</i>

01:12:51.784 --> 01:12:54.786
<i>What a day! What a day!</i>

01:13:26.026 --> 01:13:27.819
So, your explorer friend's okay?

01:13:27.903 --> 01:13:29.612
I saw him walking around town with you.

01:13:29.655 --> 01:13:32.740
Yeah, he's okay. No thanks to you.

01:13:32.825 --> 01:13:33.991
I didn't mean to be so rough on him.

01:13:34.076 --> 01:13:35.701
It's just that
I get jealous when it comes to you.

01:13:35.786 --> 01:13:37.995
- Do you?
- Christ, you know I do.

01:13:38.622 --> 01:13:40.081
I know I treat you rough. It's my way.

01:13:40.165 --> 01:13:42.834
- It doesn't mean I don't feel for you.
- Oh.

01:13:44.837 --> 01:13:46.838
- What are you doing?
- Leaving.

01:13:46.880 --> 01:13:49.048
- Here we go again.
- You don't feel for me, Monk.

01:13:49.133 --> 01:13:50.633
All you feel for is yourself!

01:13:50.676 --> 01:13:54.387
Your beer, your card games, your women!

01:13:54.471 --> 01:13:56.681
Okay, I'm gonna turn over a new leaf.

01:13:56.765 --> 01:13:59.183
- No, I'm not kidding...
- It's too late, Monk. It's too late, I'm going.

01:13:59.226 --> 01:14:01.018
I should have left a long time ago.

01:14:01.103 --> 01:14:03.521
I would have,
except I was scared of being alone.

01:14:03.605 --> 01:14:04.772
So what now?

01:14:04.857 --> 01:14:07.191
You found some chump
who's filling your head with big ideas?

01:14:07.234 --> 01:14:09.777
No, no, I got a chance to change my life.

01:14:09.862 --> 01:14:11.863
- I'm moving to Hollywood.
- All right, now listen, Cecilia,

01:14:11.905 --> 01:14:14.532
I said I was sorry
about being rough with your friend,

01:14:14.575 --> 01:14:15.616
but let's shape up!

01:14:15.701 --> 01:14:17.285
- It's too late, Monk!
- Look, like hell it...

01:14:17.369 --> 01:14:18.703
I said like hell it is!

01:14:18.787 --> 01:14:21.205
And don't be giving me
that big-headed stuff, you hear?

01:14:21.248 --> 01:14:22.790
Because I'm the guy
that can slap you down!

01:14:22.875 --> 01:14:23.958
Go ahead and hit me, Monk!

01:14:24.042 --> 01:14:25.793
Just go ahead and hit me!

01:14:25.878 --> 01:14:27.253
- I'm leaving anyway!
- Yeah, well,

01:14:27.337 --> 01:14:29.213
this never would have happened
if you didn't meet that guy.

01:14:29.298 --> 01:14:31.257
That's probably right,
and we would have just gone on

01:14:31.341 --> 01:14:34.469
the same way till we were too old
to even hope for something better.

01:14:34.553 --> 01:14:37.972
But I did meet him!
I did meet him, and I have feelings for him!

01:14:38.056 --> 01:14:40.725
- And he has for me!
- What about me?

01:14:41.602 --> 01:14:44.395
I still care for you, Monk,
if you can believe that.

01:14:44.480 --> 01:14:47.273
But out of the blue,
for the first time in my life,

01:14:47.357 --> 01:14:48.399
somebody's in love with me!

01:14:48.442 --> 01:14:50.902
No, but you just met each other.

01:14:50.944 --> 01:14:54.614
Love at first sight
doesn't only happen just in the movies.

01:14:54.698 --> 01:14:55.948
Hey, Cecilia, don't go.

01:14:56.033 --> 01:14:57.909
You hear me?
I said don't go! Now wait a minute.

01:14:57.993 --> 01:15:00.495
- Don't! I said... I said don't go!
- So long, Monk.

01:15:00.579 --> 01:15:02.622
- You stay here, you hear?
- You take care of yourself.

01:15:02.706 --> 01:15:05.666
Oh, yeah? All right, well, go, go!
See if I care.

01:15:05.751 --> 01:15:07.043
Go, see what it is out there!

01:15:07.085 --> 01:15:10.171
It ain't the movies! It's real life!

01:15:10.255 --> 01:15:12.089
It's real life, and you'll be back!

01:15:12.174 --> 01:15:14.592
You mark my words! You'll be back!

01:15:41.286 --> 01:15:42.787
Cecilia, what are you doing here?

01:15:42.871 --> 01:15:45.748
- Meeting Gil Shepherd.
- They all gone.

01:15:45.791 --> 01:15:47.083
They...

01:15:47.125 --> 01:15:48.793
What do... What do you mean?

01:15:48.877 --> 01:15:50.962
Went back to Hollywood.

01:15:51.046 --> 01:15:52.338
Gil, too?

01:15:52.422 --> 01:15:54.298
Mr. Shepherd, yeah.

01:15:54.341 --> 01:15:57.468
As soon as Tom Baxter
went back up on the movie screen,

01:15:57.553 --> 01:15:59.178
he couldn't wait to get out of here.

01:15:59.263 --> 01:16:02.139
He said this was a close call for his career.

01:16:02.891 --> 01:16:05.685
I think he's gonna play Charles Lindbergh.

01:16:13.151 --> 01:16:14.235
Don't forget, Cecilia,

01:16:14.319 --> 01:16:17.154
Fred Astaire and Ginger Rogers start today.

01:16:45.017 --> 01:16:48.853
<i>Heaven, I'm in heaven</i>

01:16:50.522 --> 01:16:56.777
<i>And my heart beats
so that I can hardly speak</i>

01:16:56.862 --> 01:17:02.450
<i>And I seem to find the happiness I seek</i>

01:17:03.243 --> 01:17:09.373
<i>When we're out together
dancing cheek to cheek</i>

01:17:10.334 --> 01:17:14.545
<i>Heaven, I'm in heaven</i>

01:17:15.881 --> 01:17:21.719
<i>And the cares that hung
around me through the week</i>

01:17:22.220 --> 01:17:27.058
<i>Seem to vanish like a gambler's lucky streak</i>

01:17:28.560 --> 01:17:34.065
<i>When we're out together
dancing cheek to cheek</i>

01:17:35.150 --> 01:17:38.235
<i>Oh, I love to climb a mountain</i>

01:17:38.320 --> 01:17:41.447
<i>And to reach the highest peak</i>

01:17:41.531 --> 01:17:45.076
<i>But it doesn't thrill me half as much</i>

01:17:45.160 --> 01:17:48.871
<i>As dancing cheek to cheek</i>

